History of Programming:

    Machine Language – Binary, error-prone, not scalable.

    Assembly Language – Mnemonics like MOV A, 61H, still low-level.

    Procedural – Loops, functions, eg. C Language.

    OOP – Real-world modeling, scalable, reusable, secure.

Objects vs Classes

    Object = Real entity (Car)

    Class = Blueprint (Car class)


Example:
    class Car {
        String brand;
        String model;

        void start() {}
        void stop() {}
    }
